    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/persian-style-spiced-beef-chuck-and-lentil-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add you <strong>diced beef </strong>to the dish with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned all over</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/persian-style-spiced-beef-chuck-and-lentil-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>red lentils</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/persian-style-spiced-beef-chuck-and-lentil-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with your <strong>curry powder </strong>and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>allspice </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/persian-style-spiced-beef-chuck-and-lentil-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato wedges </strong>with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and stir it all together</p><p>Add your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>rinsed lentils </strong>with 700ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[900ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the dish in the oven, covered, for 55 min or until the sauce has thickened, the lentils are tender and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>one pot Persian-style spiced beef chuck & lentil stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/persian-style-spiced-beef-chuck-and-lentil-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/persian-style-spiced-beef-chuck-and-lentil-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the stew is nearly ready, add your<strong> pitta[s] </strong>to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/persian-style-spiced-beef-chuck-and-lentil-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve drizzle the <strong>one pot Persian-style spiced beef chuck & lentil stew </strong>with your <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>and finish with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>warmed pitta[s] </strong>in half and serve to the side</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
